{"title": "Shot Reverse Shot", "content": "A common method of shooting dialogue: repeated Over the Shoulder shots interrupted by the occasional Medium Two-Shot.\n\nThis technique is often employed as a method of convenience; if it's impossible to get both of the actors together to film a shot, Over the Shoulder can be used with stand-ins who look, from behind, similar to the absent actor to complete the scene.\n\nThis is a standard technique from The Golden Age of Hollywood.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShotReverseShot", "media_links": ["https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MulhollandDrive", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/SteveMartin", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BetteDavis", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/HumphreyBogart", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/CharlesLaughton", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DeadMenDontWearPlaid", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/XMen1", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/StarWars", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/YasujiroOzu", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ThePattyDukeShow", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BuffyTheVampireSlayer", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Lost", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheDailyShow", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/CharlieBrooker", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Screenwipe", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/VeronicaMars", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/KristenBell"], "non_media_links": ["https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverTheShoulder", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MediumTwoShot", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverTheShoulder", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/TheGoldenAgeOfHollywood", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FilmNoir", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmw